newsitem.title: USA: US jet fuel drops on NYMEX, low-sulfur diffs slip.
newsitem.headline: US jet fuel drops on NYMEX, low-sulfur diffs slip.

text.p: U.S. spot jet fuel prices plummeted with NYMEX futures by late Wednesday, with stepped-up production pushing differentials down on low-sulfur 55-grade fuel, players said.
New York Harbor 55-grade was traded for 3.50 cents under November futures, about a half-cent weaker than Tuesday diffs, players said, with Gulf diffs easing 0.25 cent to about 0.75 cent over.
New York Harbor and Gulf 54-grade jet were stable, although falling NYMEX values drove absolute prices 2.20 cents lower, players said.
